excerpt: Roman Catholic church in Romanesque & Gothic styles, with a record breaking 22m-wide Gothic nave.
detail_description: Girona Cathedral, a Roman Catholic church in Girona, is a popular tourist attraction known for its Romanesque and Gothic architectural styles. The cathedral features a record-breaking 22-meter-wide Gothic nave. Visitors can enjoy the scenic views of the cathedral from Cafe l'Arc on Placa de la Catedrale. The old town also offers attractions such as the Cloister and the Tower of Charlemagne, dating back to the 13th century.
name: Girona Cathedral
address: Pl. de la Catedral, s/n, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Girona is a city in Spain’s northeastern Catalonia region, beside the River Onyar. It’s known for its medieval architecture, walled Old Quarter (Barri Vell) and the Roman remains of the Força Vella fortress. Landscaped gardens line the Passeig Arqueològic, a walkway following the Old Quarter’s medieval walls, which include watchtowers with sweeping views.
detail_description: Girona, located in Spain's Catalonia region, is a picturesque city known for its medieval architecture and the Roman remains of the Força Vella fortress. The walled Old Quarter features landscaped gardens and watchtowers offering sweeping views. Visitors can also enjoy the region's great foods and wines through wine tastings, picnics at family-run farms, and indulging in modern Catalan cuisine at renowned restaurants.
name: Girona
address: Spain

excerpt: Self-guided tours are offered at these preserved public baths built in the Romanesque style in 1194.
detail_description: The Arab Baths, also known as Banys Arabs, are a well-preserved public bathhouse in Girona, built in 1194. Constructed by Morisco craftsmen in the late 12th century, these baths follow the Roman model and consist of three rooms: a cold bath, a warm bath with an octagonal pool and skylight, and a steam room. The baths showcase elegant horseshoe arches and intricate stonework.
name: Arab Baths
address: Carrer del Rei Ferran el Catòlic, s/n, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Medieval church & monastery now home to an archeological museum showcasing historic relics.
detail_description: Sant Pere de Galligants is a medieval church and monastery in Girona, known for its archeological museum displaying historic relics. The site dates back to the 10th century and was once home to Benedictine monks. The monastery's church and cloister have survived through the centuries, featuring an impressive octagonal bell tower and elegant round arches that are now architectural highlights of the city.
name: Sant Pere de Galligants
address: Carrer de Santa Llúcia, 8, 17007 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Girona offers a plethora of activities, but some of the most cherished experiences include savoring wine while basking in the sun, taking in the picturesque views from the unique bridges that span the Onyar River, and indulging in delectable tapas. Consider renting a car to explore the charming nearby towns and Costa Brava coastline.
name: Onyar
address: Girona, Spain

excerpt: Large church with a mix of romanesque, gothic & baroque architecture & several sarcophagi.
detail_description: The Basílica de Sant Feliu in Girona is a stunning church that showcases a blend of Romanesque, Gothic, and Baroque architecture. It features an impressive Baroque facade, striking Gothic tower, and numerous Romanesque elements. The church is home to several notable works of art, including eight intricately carved sarcophagi and a sculpture of the Recumbent Christ by Catalan sculptor Aloi de Montbrai.
name: Basílica de Sant Feliu
address: Carrer Trasfigueres, 4, 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Plaça de la Independència is a charming square located in the heart of Girona, Spain. It is surrounded by beautiful historic buildings and lively cafes, making it a perfect spot to soak up the local atmosphere. The square is known for its vibrant energy and is a popular meeting place for both locals and tourists. With its picturesque setting and bustling surroundings, Plaça de la Independència offers visitors a true taste of Catalan culture.
name: Pl. de la Independència
address: 17001 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Rambla de la Llibertat in Girona offers a stark contrast to the narrow, confined streets of the old quarter. This wide pedestrian boulevard runs parallel to the Onyar River and is a popular spot for locals and visitors alike to shop, socialize, and enjoy a coffee. The area features beautiful shopping streets, bars, and restaurants. It's also known for its semi-pedestrian layout with various dining options and terraces perfect for relaxation.
name: Rambla de la Llibertat
address: 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: The old Jewish quarter of El Call is defined by its narrow, winding alleys and stone archways. The Jewish History Museum displays pottery and stone carvings, and hosts Sephardic concerts in its leafy courtyard. Shops along Carrer de la Forca sell books, religious jewelry, Catalan ceramics, and Kosher wine. Intimate bistros serving Jewish, Mediterranean, and Spanish cuisine dot the area, as do casual cafes and bars.
detail_description: El Call, the old Jewish quarter of Girona, is a charming area characterized by its narrow streets and stone archways. The Jewish History Museum offers a glimpse into the past with its display of pottery and stone carvings, while also hosting Sephardic concerts in its peaceful courtyard. Visitors can explore shops along Carrer de la Forca offering books, religious jewelry, Catalan ceramics, and Kosher wine.
name: El Call
address: 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: When exploring the charming streets of Girona, make sure to visit Pont de les Peixateries Velles, also known as Eiffel Bridge. This iconic bridge, dating back to 1877 and built by the renowned Eiffel et Cie company, offers a picturesque view of the colorful buildings along the Onyar river. As you cross this historic bridge, you'll be treated to a unique perspective of the city's architecture and natural beauty.
name: Pont de les Peixateries Velles
address: Carrer del Riu Onyar, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: City green space with trees, sports fields, picnic facilities & a twice-a-week street market.
detail_description: Parc de la Devesa is Catalonia's largest urban park, spanning forty hectares and offering a serene natural retreat in the heart of Girona. The park features 2,605 plane trees, open sunny spaces for sports activities, a municipal sports area, picnic spots, urban gardens, and cultural facilities like the Girona Trade Fair and Congress Centre Auditorium.
name: Parc de la Devesa
address: Passeig de la Devesa, 38, 17007 Girona, Spain

excerpt: 18th-century convent, now showcasing Girona's art & artifacts from Roman to contemporary times.
detail_description: The Museu d'Història de Girona is housed in an 18th-century convent, offering a captivating display of art and artifacts spanning from Roman times to the contemporary era. The museum's building has a rich history, transitioning from a Gothic house to a monastery for Capuchin brothers before becoming an educational institute and eventually the home of the history museum. Visitors can explore Girona's history from its Roman foundation to the Franco dictatorship era.
name: Museu d'Història de Girona
address: Carrer de la Força, 27, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Three brothers run this chic bistro known for inventive variations on traditional Catalan recipes.
detail_description: El Celler de Can Roca is a chic bistro in Costa Brava, run by the three Roca brothers. The restaurant has received numerous accolades and is known for its inventive variations on traditional Catalan recipes. It offers multi-course tasting menus with dishes like oyster with anemone sauce, garlic sand, tender walnut, and seaweeds.
name: El Celler de Can Roca
address: Carrer de Can Sunyer, 48, 17007 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Passeig de la Muralla offers a unique experience to walk along the reconstructed parts of the medieval walls, providing a scenic path around the east side of the city. The walkway allows visitors to enjoy stunning views while immersing themselves in the historical significance of the area.
name: Passeig de la Muralla
address: Girona, Spain

detail_description: If you're a fan of exploring lush green spaces, then the Jardins dels Alemanys in Girona is a must-visit. This garden is steeped in history and offers a tranquil retreat within the Old Town. The area was once home to German soldiers during the Peninsular War, and remnants of their barracks can still be seen. The Lightning Tower provides stunning panoramic views of Girona, making it a perfect spot for photography enthusiasts.
name: Jardins dels Alemanys
address: Carrer de la Muralla, 2, 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Rocambolesc Gelateria is a vibrant and whimsical ice cream and candy store located in the heart of Girona. Founded by the Roca brothers, who are also behind the renowned El Celler de Can Roca, this confectionary shop aims to bring the delightful desserts of their world-famous restaurant to a wider audience. The gelateria offers an array of ever-changing ice cream flavors such as caramelized baked apple, coconut and lavender, and cherry and lime sorbet.
name: Rocambolesc Gelateria | Girona
address: Carrer de Sta. Clara, 50, 17001 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Venerable 9th-century city walls with walkways, towers & scenic vantage points of the area.
detail_description: The Muralles de Girona, also known as the City Walls of Girona, are ancient fortifications dating back to the 9th century. Walking along these walls provides breathtaking panoramic views of the Old Town, River Onyar, and the surrounding countryside. The route includes several lookout points offering different perspectives of the city and mountains, making it an ideal spot for watching sunsets.
name: Muralles de Girona
address: Carrer dels Alemanys, 20, 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: The Convent of Sant Domènec is a historic site in Girona, known for its iconic Gothic architecture dating back to the 13th-14th centuries. The convent features a remarkable church, chapterhouse, and a spacious cloister. Nearby stands the Les Aligues building from the 16th century, showcasing rare Renaissance design. This area also houses the Humanities campus and Rectors Office of the university.
name: Convent of Sant Domènec
address: Plaça de Sant Domènec, 11, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Historical palace-turned-museum with a collection ranging from Romanesque art to current-day pieces.
detail_description: The Museu d'Art de Girona is located in the historic Episcopal Palace, a stunning 12th-century stone building. It was established in 1976 by merging the Diocesan Museum of Girona and the Provincial Museum of Antiques and Fine Arts. The museum's extensive collection boasts nearly 14,000 works spanning from Romanesque art to contemporary pieces.
name: Museu d'Art de Girona
address: Pujada de la Catedral, 12, 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Pl. de la Catedral is a charming square located in the heart of Girona, Spain. It is surrounded by beautiful historic buildings and offers stunning views of the Girona Cathedral. The square is a popular spot for both locals and tourists to relax and take in the picturesque surroundings. Visitors can also explore nearby cafes, restaurants, and shops while enjoying the lively atmosphere of this vibrant area. With its rich history and architectural beauty, Pl.
name: Pl. de la Catedral
address: 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Museum with Jewish history exhibits ranging from the religion's origin to culture, plus a gift shop.
detail_description: The Museu d'Història dels Jueus, located in the Bonastruc ca Porta centre in Girona, is a museum dedicated to showcasing the history and culture of Catalonia's Jewish communities. Housed in a former synagogue, the museum features 11 rooms that provide insight into the daily lives and traditions of medieval Jewish communities in Girona and the surrounding region.
name: Museu d'Història dels Jueus
address: Carrer de la Força, 8, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Cinema history artifacts from 1800s to 1970, with movie cameras, photos & Chinese shadow theater.
detail_description: The Museu del Cinema-Col·lecció Tomàs Mallol in Girona is a treasure trove of cinema history, showcasing artifacts from the 1800s to 1970. Visitors can explore movie cameras, photos, and even Chinese shadow theater.
name: Museu del Cinema-Col·lecció Tomàs Mallol
address: Carrer de la Sèquia, 1, 17001 Girona, Spain

detail_description: La Lleona, a colonnaded statue of a lioness located in the old town near the river in Girona, holds a special ritual where visitors kiss the lion's bottom to show respect. The statue has an iron staircase allowing people to reach buttock level for this tradition. Nearby, El Call, the well-preserved Jewish Quarter, offers charming streets and a glimpse into its historical significance. Visitors can also enjoy dining at nearby restaurants with varied menus and friendly service.
name: El Cul de la Lleona
address: Carrer dels Calderers, 8, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Founded in the 11th century, this monastery with lush surrounds features guided tours & old artwork.
detail_description: Sant Daniel Monastery, located just outside Girona, is a historic site founded in the 11th century by Countess Ermessenda of Carcassonne. Nestled in the lush Sant Daniel Valley, it offers guided tours and showcases old artwork. The monastery is dedicated to Saint Daniel and has been a place of worship for nearly a thousand years.
name: Sant Daniel Monastery
address: Carrer de les Monges, 2, 17007 Girona, Spain

detail_description: The Pont de Pedra, also known as the Stone Bridge or Pont d'Isabel II, was constructed during the reign of Queen Isabel II. Visitors can enjoy browsing through craft stalls offering locally made products such as snacks, handmade soaps, jewelry, and souvenirs. The bridge offers stunning views and is a great spot for a leisurely 15 to 30-minute visit at any time of day.
name: Pont de Pedra
address: Girona, Spain

detail_description: Girona Temps de Flors is an annual event that takes place in May, offering visitors the chance to explore the city's old town adorned with stunning floral art installations. The festival provides a unique opportunity to discover privately owned spaces typically closed to the public, all free of charge. Girona itself is a charming city, but during Temps de Flors, it becomes even more enchanting as it blooms with vibrant colors and creative displays.
name: Girona Temps de Flors
address: 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Girona Old Town Apartment is located in the most captivating part of the city, just a short walk from the bridge. The area is rich in history and charm, offering visitors a glimpse into the city's past. It's a place where you can truly immerse yourself in the local culture and experience the authentic atmosphere of Girona.
name: Girona Old Town Apartment
address: Plaça de Sant Pere, 2, 17007 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Pujada de Sant Domènec, also known as the steps of Braavos in Game of Thrones, is a picturesque location that served as the setting for the market scenes in the series. The impressive Girona Cathedral was featured as the Great Sept of Baelor. Upon visiting these sites and comparing them to their on-screen depictions, it becomes evident that CGI played a significant role in bringing these locations to life on television.
name: Pujada de Sant Domènec
address: 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Modest display of archaeological exhibits & sculptures in a grand former monastery.
detail_description: Nestled within the stunning Monestir de Sant Pere Galligants, the Museu d'Arqueologia de Catalunya in Girona offers a captivating glimpse into the region's rich history. This museum showcases an impressive array of archaeological artifacts and sculptures that span from prehistory to the Middle Ages. Visitors can marvel at remnants from Empuries, Roman headstones, and medieval inscriptions that tell stories of Girona's past.
name: Museu d'Arqueologia de Catalunya | Girona
address: Carrer de Santa Llúcia, 8, 17007 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Historical palace-turned-museum with a collection ranging from Romanesque art to current-day pieces.
name: Museu d'Art de Girona
address: Pujada de la Catedral, 12, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Birthplace of renowned architect Rafael Maso, with 19th-century furnishings & sweeping city views.
detail_description: Fundació Rafael Masó / Casa Masó is the birthplace of the renowned architect Rafael Maso Valenti, located in Girona. The house features 19th-century furnishings and offers sweeping city views, including a stunning view of the colorful houses overlooking the River Onyar and the Cathedral from Pont de Sant Feliu and Pont d'en Gomez. The building's furniture and decoration represent the Noucentisme style, a Catalan reaction to modernism.
name: Fundació Rafael Masó / Casa Masó
address: Carrer de les Ballesteries, 29, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Landscaped urban park with open lawns, an ornamental lake & a bar, plus swings & a sandbox for kids.
name: Cafè del Parc
address: Carrer Migdia, s/n, 17003 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Estadi Montilivi is a beautiful stadium with visible floodlight masts that create an exciting atmosphere for football enthusiasts. The seating offers excellent views close to the field, providing a great vantage point to enjoy the game and soak in the vibrant ambiance. The family-friendly environment outside the stadium allows fans to mingle before matches, offering various food and drink options. Additionally, visitors can appreciate stunning views of the mountains and sunset from the stadium.
name: Estadi Montilivi
address: Avinguda de Montilivi, 141, 17003 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Located in Girona, Spain, Torre Gironella stands at the highest point of the Roman Wall and is one of the city's oldest landmarks. Initially a defensive tower, it provided refuge for the persecuted Jewish community in 1391. Visitors can enjoy stunning views over Girona and its skyline, including the nearby basilica bell tower.
name: Torre Gironella
address: Carrer de la Muralla, 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: The Monument to Carles Rahola, created by Francesc Torres Monso in 1959 and dedicated to Carles Rahola in 1978, bears an inscription that emphasizes the importance of preserving the sacredness and uniqueness of Girona. While the text on the sculpture may not be easily readable, it conveys a powerful message: let there never be another place in this world where oppressive structures like gallows are allowed to rise again within Girona's cherished domain.
name: Monument a Carles Rahola
address: 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Casa Pastors is an old house with interesting exhibitions inside. It can be difficult to get in, but it's worth it if you're interested in art.
name: Casa Pastors
address: Pl. de la Catedral, 2, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Arts & cultural center hosting rotating exhibitions, workshops for kids & music concerts.
detail_description: The CaixaForum Girona is an arts centre with rotating exhibitions, workshops for kids, and music concerts. It's housed in the National Historic Monument building Fontana d'Or, and is more than just a gallery - it's also a whole arts centre.
name: CaixaForum Girona
address: Carrer dels Ciutadans, 19, 17004 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Cozy cultural space featuring exhibitions with diverse themes, including design, science & the arts.
detail_description: The venue is a cultural space that showcases exhibitions with diverse themes, including design, science & the arts. It is also an official business venue.
name: Espai Santa Caterina
address: Pça. Pompeu Fabra, 1, 17002 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Capella de Sant Nicolau is a significant piece of religious architecture in Girona, representing the Romanesque style of the Catalan Middle Ages. The temple, with its basilical plan and captivating capitals in the central nave and cloister, showcases the grandeur and iconographic interest of this 12th-century Benedictine monastery. Today, it serves as a museum and exhibition hall, allowing visitors to appreciate both its exterior Romanesque beauty and the art within its thick walls.
name: Capella de Sant Nicolau
address: Carrer de Santa Llúcia, 10, 17007 Girona, Spain

detail_description: The Torre de Santo Domingo, a cylindrical structure attached to the city walls of Girona, offers panoramic views of the entire city. Ascending the narrow spiral metal staircase grants visitors a 360-degree perspective. Despite some individuals feeling apprehensive about navigating the dark room beneath the tower and its steep stairs, it is still worth making the trip for these breathtaking vistas.
name: Torre de Santo Domingo
address: Carrer de la Muralla, 9, 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: The Parish Church of Santa Susanna del Mercadal, situated in Placa de Santa Susanna in Girona, is a spacious and beautiful church dating back to the 14th and 15th centuries. It underwent reconstruction in the 20th century. The interior of the church showcases an array of altarpieces and chapels dedicated to various virgin figures.
name: Parròquia de Santa Susanna del Mercadal
address: Carrer de l'Obra, 6, 17001 Girona, Spain

name: Monument als defensors de Girona el 1808 i 1809
address: 17001 Girona, Spain

detail_description: GALERIA D'ART EL CLAUSTRE is an art gallery located in the historic center of the city. It showcases a variety of both modern and historical exhibitions mostly in the mediums of painting and sculpture. The atmosphere is very nice, and the gallery is small so it's easy to get around.
name: GALERIA D'ART EL CLAUSTRE
address: Carrer Nou, 8, 17001 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Pont de Sant Feliu is a modern bridge in Girona, built in 1995, serving as an entrance to the old town. It connects Devesa Park with Saint Feliu Square and offers a stunning view of the Church of Sant Feliu. The bridge's architecture and nighttime lighting make it a beautiful sight over the Onyar River.
name: Pont de Sant Feliu
address: 17001 Girona, Spain

name: Monument al rei Jaume I
address: Gran Via de Jaume I, 29, 17001 Girona, Spain

detail_description: The Torre Del Llamp, also known as the Tower of the Lightning, is a Carolingian-era tower situated in the highest area of the medieval wall of Girona. It is part of the old Roman Walls and offers a spectacular view of the city. The name "Tower of the Lightning" pays homage to Jupiter, with a small sculpture inside depicting the god of lightning. Visitors can enjoy breathtaking panoramas from this historical site, making it a must-visit for panoramic enthusiasts.
name: Torre Del Llamp (o del Telègraf)
address: Carrer dels Alemanys, 20, 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: Estatua de los deseos Pisada de san Narciso is a significant attraction located in the historic center of Girona. It takes the form of the footprint of the city's patron saint and holds a legendary belief that touching it and making a wish will make it come true. This Roman-style sculpture, situated near the Church of Sant Feliu, is said to have been crafted by a specialized store in marble and similar materials.
name: Estatua de los deseos Pisada de san Narciso
address: Carrer del Pou Rodó, 5, 17004 Girona, Spain

detail_description: In the charming city of Girona, Spain, you'll find a collection of architectural landmarks that showcase the city's rich history and artistic heritage. One such landmark is Farinera Teixidor, a palatial home designed by renowned local architect Rafael Maso in 1910. This modernist building is an iconic representation of Girona's architectural legacy and is included in the Inventory of the Architectural Heritage of Catalonia.
name: Farinera Teixidor
address: Carrer de Santa Eugènia, 42, 17005 Girona, Spain

excerpt: Portion of art museum featuring an old hospital pharmacy, chapel & inner courtyard.
detail_description: The Antic Hospital de Santa Caterina, located in the old town of Girona, is a historical site that served as a hospital from the 15th century until the 21st century. This Gothic building features an ancient pharmacy from the 18th century, one of the best-preserved in southern Europe. The complex includes two cloisters, a church, a chapter house, and a library. Today it houses cultural and service buildings with a blend of ancient remnants and modern architecture.
name: Antic Hospital de Santa Caterina
address: Pça. Pompeu Fabra, 1, 17002 Girona, Spain

name: Font dels Lledoners
address: 17004 Girona, Spain
